Ondo State Deputy Governor, Agboola Ajayi, has boasted that he will defeat Governor Rotimi Akeredolu, on Saturday. Ajayi is the flagbearer of Zenith Labour Party (ZLP). He spoke on Wednesday in Owo Local Government Area during his campaign tour. Ajayi expressed confidence on victory, adding that he will be declared winner of the governorship poll. On violence, he told security agencies to protect lives and property. The deputy governor appealed to residents not to panic. Ajayi advised his supporters not to take arms but go out and vote. “We are here to campaign. We are not here to fight anybody. Please, don’t allow anybody to provoke you. Vote and protect your votes,” NAN quoted him as saying.